    answer: "Plasmolysis is the process in which the protoplasm (living contents) of a plant cell shrinks and pulls away from the cell wall due to the loss of water by osmosis, when the cell is placed in a hypertonic solution (a solution more concentrated than the cell's contents).\n\nIn a hypertonic solution:\n• The external solution has a higher solute concentration (lower water concentration) than the cell's cytoplasm and vacuole.\n• Water moves out of the cell by osmosis through the selectively permeable plasma membrane.\n• The vacuole and cytoplasm shrink.\n• The plasma membrane pulls away from the rigid cell wall, creating a visible gap between the membrane and the wall.\n• The cell becomes flaccid (loses turgor).\n\nThe cell wall does NOT shrink — it is rigid and remains in place.",
