    question: "State two functions of the cell wall in plant cells.",
    answer: "Two functions of the cell wall in plant cells:\n\n1. Mechanical support and shape: The rigid cellulose cell wall gives the plant cell a definite, fixed shape and provides structural support to the plant. It prevents the cell from collapsing or changing shape under physical stress. In hypotonic conditions, the cell wall exerts wall pressure (opposing turgor pressure), preventing the cell from bursting when it absorbs water.\n\n2. Protection: The cell wall protects the cell against mechanical injury, infection by pathogens, and osmotic lysis. It acts as a physical barrier between the cell and its environment. In very dilute (hypotonic) solutions, the cell wall prevents the cell from bursting by resisting the outward pressure of turgid contents.",
